parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Corrosion and Rust on Frame and Body
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive corrosion and rust on the frame and body of the vehicle can cause structural failure, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud clunking or banging noises
uneven tire wear
difficulty steering
and visible signs of rust and corrosion on the frame and body.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Rear Shock Mount and Lower Control Arm
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear shock mount and lower control arm can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud clunking or banging noises
uneven tire wear
difficulty steering
and visible signs of rust and corrosion on the rear shock mount and lower control arm.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Front Lower Control Arm
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front lower control arm can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud clunking or banging noises
uneven tire wear
difficulty steering
and visible signs of rust and corrosion on the front lower control arm.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly
without warning
and may not respond to braking. The accelerator pedal may become stuck
and the vehicle may surge forward
even when the driver is not pressing the pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control system can lead to unintended acceleration, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to disengage
causing the vehicle to continue accelerating even when the driver is not pressing the pedal. The vehicle may not respond to braking
and the accelerator pedal may become stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle cable can lead to unintended acceleration, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The throttle cable becomes stuck
causing the accelerator pedal to stick or become unresponsive. The vehicle may surge forward
even when the driver is not pressing the pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion or rust of the subframe can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit unusual noises
vibrations
or movements
such as a loud banging or creaking sound
while driving. The subframe may fracture or break
causing the vehicle to lose control or become unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion or rust of the rear wheel well can cause the shock absorber to break loose, leading to loss of control, accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit unusual noises
such as a rattling or banging sound
while driving. The rear wheel well may have visible signs of rust or corrosion
and the shock absorber may be loose or detached.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion or rust of the front subframe crossbrace can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit unusual noises
vibrations
or movements
such as a loud creaking or groaning sound
while driving. The front subframe crossbrace may fracture or break
causing the vehicle to lose control or become unstable.
